text: :This article is about the frog from New Guinea. For the frog from Tanzania, see Leptopelis vermiculatus. Ranoidea exophthalmia (also known as the big-eyed tree frog) is a tree frog from New Guinea. Scientists found it between 730 and 850 meters above sea level. ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Ranoidea exophthalmia
